  "note_summaries": {
    "1": "A-1/A-1M values are basic allowable tensile stresses. For pressure design, apply the applicable quality factor E.",
    "3": "Austenitic stainless stress values may not apply if final heat treatment differs from the material specification or specified table notes.",
    "6": "Minimum temperature column is the normally suitable design minimum temperature without additional impact testing, subject to Code impact-test rules.",
    "11": "Radiography is required after heat treatment for use under the Code.",
    "26": "Unstabilized stainless grades have increasing intergranular carbide precipitation tendency as carbon exceeds 0.03 percent.",
    "28": "Above 538 degC, these stresses apply only when carbon content is 0.04 percent or higher.",
    "30": "Above 538 degC, these stresses require heat treatment at minimum 1093 degC followed by water quench or rapid cooling.",
    "31": "Above 538 degC, these stresses require heat treatment at minimum 1038 degC followed by water quench or rapid cooling.",
    "36": "Welded pipe entry. Use appropriate longitudinal weld joint quality factor from Table A-1B/para. 302.3.4.",
    "51": "Special welding qualification consideration may be required. A qualified WPS is required for each strength level.",
    "55": "Pipe is not intended for high-temperature service. Listed stresses apply only to stated production/condition basis.",
    "57": "Graphitization risk after prolonged exposure above 427 degC.",
    "59": "For temperatures above 482 degC, consider killed steel.",
    "67": "Stress row is tied to plate-based welded pipe specification basis. Verify plate grade/backing specification and pipe class in MTC.",
    "71": "Microalloying and supplementary chemistry/weldability/toughness controls may be required.",
    "72": "For service temperature above 454 degC, weld metal carbon shall exceed 0.05 percent.",
    "75": "P22 values are for normalized and tempered condition or unknown heat treatment. If annealed, use the separate lower high-temperature values in the Code.",
    "77": "CSA Z245.1 grades listed in the Code may be treated as API 5L equivalents.",
    "4b": "A-1M font style distinguishes tensile-controlled, yield-controlled, and time-dependent values."
  },
